net.objectof.facet

Interface Facet<T extends Annotated>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The object type associated to this facet. Generally T will be a Faceted.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Named
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IAttributedFacet, IBaseMetamodel, ICompositeTemplate, IFacet, IFacets, IInterfaceTemplate, IMetamodel, IPackageFacets, IPackageTemplate, IPropertiesTemplate, IResourceTemplate, ITemplate

    public interface Facet<T extends Annotated>
extends Named
    A Facet defines a set of attributes that can be associated to a Faceted object though Property objects and provides the ability to process the Faceted object at compile time. The general approach for Processing is to generate zero or more artifacts through templating of the metadata.
    Author:
    jdh
